<TEXT>
the us supreme court refused 
wednesday to stay the execution of a convicted child killer 
scheduled to die thursday morning after his attorneys lost similar 
appeals in three lower courts 
the emergency request by aubrey dennis adams jr was denied by 
the high court in a 72 vote the justices also turned down his 
formal appeal to review his death sentence 
justices william j brennan and thurgood marshall who oppose 
the death penalty in all circumstances voted to spare adams 
earlier wednesday the 11th us circuit court of appeals in 
atlanta denied a request for a stay of execution for adams saying 
it didnt find merit in any of the claims raised 
the 11th circuits decision wednesday night followed rejection 
of adams appeal by the florida supreme court in the morning and by 
us district judge john h moore ii in the afternoon 
the supreme court appeal was filed in anticipation of the lower 
court rejections said larry spalding head of the state agency 
that handles final appeals for inmates facing execution 
adams 31 a former officer at marion correctional institution 
in ocala was originally scheduled to die tuesday for the murder of 
an 8yearold marion county girl but the state supreme court 
issued a 48hour stay monday 
he is scheduled to die in the electric chair at florida state 
prison near starke at 7 am edt thursday 
if adams is put to death he will be the second man executed in 
the state this year and the 21st since florida resumed executions 
in 1979 in january ted bundy was executed for killing a lake city 
schoolgirl the last in a string a serial killings that started in 
the pacific northwest 
adams is under his fourth death warrant for the jan 23 1978 
murder of trisa gail thornley a thirdgrader last seen on her way 
home from school 
the girls mutilated and naked body was found in a plastic bag 
march 15 1978 by hunters in a remote area about three miles from 
her home 
an obscene phone call to the girls home was traced to adams 
home and he eventually admitted picking her up he said he recalls 
that she screamed at some point he placed his hand over her mouth 
to silence her and she suffocated 
adams and his wife a teachers aide were friends of the 
victims parents 
he had been scheduled to die in 1984 and twice in 1986 when 
three psychiatrists ruled him mentally competent to be executed 
state law requires that inmates be able to understand why they are 
being punished before they can be executed 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

