<DOCNO> AP890503-0002 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a chemical fire in an electronics plant 
tuesday released an acid gas and 19 people were hospitalized 
authorities said 
the fire that started in chemical processing equipment at 
advanced dielectrics incs circuit board plant filled the sky with 
hydrogen bromide fumes before being brought under control around 
430 pm said cathleen shonk of the fremont fire department 
hydrogen bromide is an acid gas that is extremely irritating to 
the nose and throat when inhaled shonk said the cause of the fire 
was being investigated 
orange smoke filled the plants halls the fire department 
evacuated about 100 employees and 225 workers from the sequoia 
institute a training center next door to the factory in an 
industrial park 
the 19 injured were taken to hospitals in fremont and hayward 
cities along the eastern shore of the san francisco bay north of 
san jose 
four people were listed in stable condition at kaiser hospital 
in hayward the hospital would not disclose the nature of their 
injuries 
nine patients were taken to washington hospital in fremont 
where they were given 15minute decontamination showers and awaited 
examinations for possible respiratory damage said spokeswoman 
patricia mcauliffe 
six people treated at saint rose hospital in hayward for 
irritation to their eyes and throat were in stable condition and 
were expected to be released tuesday evening said spokesman robert 
thorn 
another 16 people were treated at the scene for smoke 
irritation said shonk 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

