<TEXT>
a picasso selfportrait a town house by philip 
johnson and andy warhols shot red marilyn are among the 4529 
artworks going on the block here during a 12day 600 million 
auction frenzy that got under way tuesday night 
sothebys and christies the citys biggest auction houses 
hope to ring up 572 million in sales and habsburg feldman a 
genevabased auctioneer was expecting to bring in up to 305 
million for 57 impressionist and modern paintings 
there is a tremendous amount of interest and purchasing power 
around the world said john l marion chairman of sothebys 
north america there is heavy buying from europeans and 
tremendous interest from the far east especially japan korean 
buyers are now emerging and i would not count the americans out 
either 
sothebys and christies were to auction 4472 works starting 
with contemporary art sales this week 
among the paintings sold tuesday night at sothebys were two 
major drip paintings by jackson pollock number 8 1950 which 
went for 105 million and number 19 1949 which fetched 36 
million 
the price paid for number 8 1950 broke the record for a 
pollock painting 572 million last year for frieze 
jeffrey deitch who bought number 8 for an anonymous 
collector called the price very advantageous sometimes you 
just get lucky 
triptych mayjune done by francis bacon in 1973 and 
inspired by the suicide of the artists close friend george dyer 
sold for 57 million 
five sculptures by claes oldenburg were sold ice cream 
sandwich 370000 plate of meat 360000 bacon and 
egg 450000 cheesecake from javatime 47500 and green 
beans 240000 
andy warhols red jackie which portrays a rubylipped 
jacqueline kennedy onassis as first lady in 1963 sold for 750000 
more than twice the presale estimate 
red marilyn a 1964 depiction of marilyn monroe will be 
offered at christies on wednesday the estimate for the signed 
synthetic polymer silkscreen on canvas is 15 million to 2 
million 
other christies offerings include colored alphabet a 
12by10 inch oil and paper collage by jasper johns estimated at 
15 million the theme is in fact the alphabet but its in 
vivid overlapping colors various shades of blue yellow and red 
with some black said roberta maneker a christies spokeswoman 
a sotheby sale next tuesday features gauguins mata mua 
circa 1892 completed during the artists first trip to tahiti 
estimated at 20 million to 25 million it is being sold by jaime 
ortizpatino heir to a bolivian tin fortune and baron hans 
heinrich thyssenbornemisza a member of the advisory board of 
sothebys holdings 
the same day yo picasso a 1901 selfportrait done in paris 
during the artists blue period is expected to command 15 
million to 20 million the seller is wendell cherry president and 
chief executive officer of humana inc the louisville ky 
hospital management corporation 
a jackson pollock triptych a series of three drip paintings on 
three canvasses in black red and yellow is expected to fetch 15 
million to 25 million 
a sothebys sale of 20th century decorative arts saturday will 
include the only town house designed by architect philip johnson 
the twostory minimalist house was commissioned in 1950 by mrs 
john d rockefeller iii andy warhol called it the original new 
york loft real estate taxes on it in 1988 came to 14414 
a christies impressionist sale on may 10 and may 11 is expected 
to bring in 109 million to 149 million 
the paintings include five monets including the trees 
autumn estimated at 6 million to 8 million seven picassos 10 
renoirs including the logue 25 million to 35 million 
which depicts a model and renoirs brother edmond a journalist 
peering through opera glasses and four by degas 
the private collection of late movie producer hal b wallis 
including two monets will be auctioned next week 
sothebys is shooting for total sales of 2609 million to 
3408 million christies aims for 1699 million to 2313 
million 
