where most students take the act mississippi was came up 28th or 
last with an average score of 162 
mississippi also ranked last this time among all the states 
in perpupil spending the state spent 2350 per student in 1988 
alaska was the highest at 8010 followed by new york at 6497 
the wall chart also compares states on teacher salaries 
pupilteacher ratios and education reform efforts alaskan teachers 
were paid the highest in 1988 40424 while south dakotans were 
at the bottom with 19758 the national average last year was 
28008 up from 19274 in 1982 
