an adult community has won the 
right to evict a toddler in a test of a federal law aimed at 
preventing age discrimination in housing 
pasco circuit judge lawrence keough gave vincent malloy 30 days 
to remove his son johnny who turns 2 this week from arborwood at 
summertree a 289unit community for adults 55 and older 
after a threehour nonjury trial keough decided tuesday that 
the subdivision fits exceptions to the newly amended fair housing 
act which took effect march 12 and upheld the associations age 
restriction as legal 
the law includes exemptions for retirement communities if 80 
percent of the households have at least one person age 55 or older 
and if facilities and services are provided for them 
arborwood attorney michael brudny said the subdivision meets 
both requirements 
