pope john paul ii on wednesday lamented 
that children are dying in africa and elsewhere in the third world 
because their governments are forced to spend their scarce cash on 
debt repayment 
in a speech to diplomats the pope appealed for new and 
courageous action by creditor nations to ease the 
multibilliondollar debt burdens of the worlds poorest nations 
the pope also kept up his attack on apartheid appealed for 
