erickson occupies a prized 12acre site opposite the national 
gallery of art 
a smiling baker held the ribbon draped across the main entrance 
to the building while mulroney clipped it with a pair of scissors 
before a crowd of dignitaries that included leading members of 
congress supreme court justice harry a blackmun and cia director 
william webster 
baker said the new embassy conveys the warmth and openness of 
the people of canada and reflects enduring bonds of friendship 
between the two countries 
mulroney declared the embassy open in the service of canada 
and in service of the friendship of our great ally the united 
states of america 
together they visited ambassador derek burneys glassedin 
penthouse office suite on the sixth floor to admire the view of the 
mall and the capitol 
the embassy staff of 327 people moved into the building a month 
ago from their previous quarters in two buildings on massachusetts 
avenue the citys traditional embassy row and rented space in 
a downtown office building 
burney who arrived shortly before bush was inaugurated jan 20 
will continue to reside in an elegant sixstory mansion on 
massachusetts avenue where canadas envoys had maintained their 
offices since 1928 
the new embassy building finished in ontario limestone with 
unpolished aluminum pillars was completed in march a year behind 
schedule at a cost of 76 million nearly double the original 
estimate 
the courtyard outside the main entrance features a pool 
terraced greenery and a fountain under a rotunda circled by 12 
columns one for each of canadas 10 provinces and two territories 
inside are a 20000volume library a 175seat theater a small 
exercise room and an art gallery 
</TEXT>
