jim colbert once earned a living by artfully 
whacking a little ball across expansive green lawns and sandy 
gullies seldom thinking about the battles with mother nature that 
go into golf course designs 
now that hes switched from pro to proprietor he thinks of 
little else 
today jim colbert golf inc owns or operates 14 public and 
private golf courses from california to florida with the number 
expected to expand into the 20s by the end of the year 
colbert is rolling now but hes learned the hard way that 
weather can make or break a good golf operation 
this whole business evolves around water colbert 48 said 
in an interview you may be plagued with too much or too little 
once a course is built the only thing left is drainage drainage 
drainage whether its yours or the lords 
with our courses in louisiana the problem is too much water 
in las vegas its too little 
the exception was in 1984 when a rare las vegas flood swamped a 
course where colberts fledgling company had spent 1 million in 
remodeling work 
it took 15 million and two years to fix it up colbert 
said of damage to the old countyrun winterwood golf course that 
was our welcome to the golf course business 
today colberts company has 500 employees at courses in nine 
states 
colbert credits a bad back and a decade of duty on the 10member 
pga tour policy board with nudging him into the golf course 
business 
he served with the leaders of giant corporations learning how 
to build companies and golf courses by the time he left the board 
in 1984 the organization had built 12 tpc the players club 
courses 
the courses are used as a pga tournament course once a year and 
the remainder of the year as public or private courses they are 
operated by the pga tour and are very good profit centers for the 
tour colbert said 
being involved in the building of these courses peeked my 
interest in golf courses colbert recalled 
colbert won his first pro title in 1969 by the time nagging 
back problems forced him to the sidelines 18 years later he had 
won eight tournaments and more than 15 million in prize money 
i didnt play half the time colbert said of a fouryear 
span beginning in 1976 when the back problems intensified it 
looked like my career was over 
a native of elizabeth nj colbert grew up in the kansas city 
suburb of prairie village kan and attended kansas state 
university in manhattan on a football scholarship from 1959 to 
1964 honing his golf skills as well 
